  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Typhoon Ruby (Hagupit) Response in Marinduque</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- shelter of most affected repaired and debris cleared
- livelihoods restarted 
- food and other non food needs during planting season are met
- Lessons learned inform MACEC, LGUs and communities&apos; DRR/CCA plans</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will respond primarily to the recovery of livelihoods (the sector that was most affected by strong winds and rains) of vulnerable farming and fishing households affected by Typhoon Hagupit in December 2014.

Activities will include the ff.:
- community preparation and mobilisation 
- cash for work - for debris clearing, coastal clean ups and declogging 
- cash grant for shelter repairs
- distribution of certified seeds (rice, vegetables, etc.) and rootcrops for recovery and to encourage diversification
- capacity building/refresher for MACEC staff on humanitarian standards and cash transfer programming and other response modalities, where needed</narrative>
  </description>
